cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.NA 

This paper discusses the use of MapReduce, a distributed computing framework, for processing large astronomical image datasets. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves data management and storage, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper discusses image processing and optimization techniques, which could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CR (Computer Graphics). Finally, the paper involves numerical analysis and simulation, which could fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
